overview: >-
  The user initiated a request to fix a pull request with multiple issues,
  including critical security vulnerabilities, various bugs, and failing Vercel
  deployments. The agent began by thoroughly reviewing the PR comments and CI
  logs to identify all problems. Key issues included a trivially forgeable admin
  authentication cookie, insecure API pagination, memory issues with CSV export,
  incorrect PDF metric calculations, and hardcoded values.

  The agent systematically addressed these concerns. A major security overhaul
  involved replacing the insecure 'true' cookie with a robust HMAC-signed
  session system, which was later adapted to use the Web Crypto API to ensure
  compatibility with Vercel's Edge Runtime for middleware. Data handling was
  improved by adding validation and pagination to API routes and the CSV export.
  PDF generation bugs, such as  values and incorrect time calculations,
  were fixed, and the "Download PDF" button was made functional. Additionally,
  number input fields were updated to correctly handle null values, and Zod
  schemas were enhanced with regex validation for time inputs. After
  implementing all fixes, the agent ensured local linting and building passed,
  and proactively addressed the Edge Runtime compatibility issue before final
  deployment.
